folder., 405: Returned when the method was not allowed.}

@endpoint POST /folders/{folder_id}/metadata/enterprise/securityClassification-6VMVochwUWo
@desc Add classification to folder
@required {folder_id: str # The unique identifier that represent a folder.  The ID for any folder can be determined by visiting this folder in the web application and copying the ID from the URL. For example, for the URL `https://*.app.box.com/folder/123` the `folder_id` is `123`.  The root folder of a Box account is always represented by the ID `0`.}
@optional {Box__Security__Classification__Key: str # The name of the classification to apply to this folder.  To list the available classifications in an enterprise, use the classification API to retrieve the [classification template](e://get_metadata_templates_enterprise_securityClassification-6VMVochwUWo_schema) which lists all available classification keys.}
@returns(201) {$canEdit: bool, $parent: str, $scope: str, $template: str, $type: str, $typeVersion: num, $version: int, Box__Security__Classification__Key: str} # Returns the classification template instance
